SIMPLE: reproducer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reproducer
<hw>Re`pro*du"cer</hw> <pr>(-d?"s?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who, or that which, reproduces.</def>
<rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a phonograph, a device containing a sounding
diaphragm and the needle or stylus that traverses the moving record, for
reproducing the sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In a manograph, a device for reproducing the engine
stroke on a reduced scale.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reproduction</ent>⟦br⟧
